# 4. Data Model

The system consists of five primary entities.

- Event
- Team
- Member
- Score
- Administrator

---

# 5. Entity Descriptions

## Event

Represents a competition event.

Attributes

| Attribute | Type | Description |
|------------|------|-------------|
| eventId | String | Unique event identifier |
| eventName | String | Name of the event |
| eventDate | Date | Competition date |
| registrationDeadline | DateTime | Closing time |
| status | String | Open or Closed |

---

## Team

Represents a participating team.

| Attribute | Type | Description |
|------------|------|-------------|
| teamId | String | Unique identifier |
| teamName | String | Team name |
| score | Integer | Current score |
| position | Integer | Leaderboard position |

---

## Member

Represents an individual participant.

| Attribute | Type | Description |
|------------|------|-------------|
| memberId | String | Unique identifier |
| fullName | String | Participant name |
| email | String | Email address |
| phone | String | Contact number |

---

## Administrator

Represents an authorised organiser.

| Attribute | Type | Description |
|------------|------|-------------|
| adminId | String | Administrator ID |
| username | String | Login username |
| password | String | Encrypted password |

---

## Score

Represents a score update.

| Attribute | Type | Description |
|------------|------|-------------|
| scoreId | String | Unique identifier |
| teamId | String | Team being updated |
| points | Integer | Points awarded |
| timestamp | DateTime | Update time |

---

